<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 18 at 5:29AM EDT  by NWS NorthernIndiana</headline>
<description>...BRIEF PERIOD OF HEAVIER SNOW THIS MORNING...
A band of moderate to briefly heavy snow is expected to affect
areas roughly along and south of the US Route 24 corridor across
north central and northeast Indiana along with northwest Ohio.
Visibilities will drop to less than one half of a mile briefly as
this band shifts from west to east through 10 AM EDT. While snow
accumulations will be generally less than an inch with this band
this morning, brief heavier snowfall rates and gusty west winds
to 20 to 30 mph may result in some slick spots on roads along with
reduced visibilities. If travelling this morning, be prepared for
deteriorating travel conditions as this band shifts eastward.</description>
